The K-nearest algorithm is a learning method based on states, so it doesn’t want a learning stage. It treats with the training pattern that is related to a distance function and the choice of the class function based on the classes of the nearest neighbors [41, 42]. When a new pattern is classified, it must be compared to others using a similarity measure taking into consideration the k-neighbors. The distance between the new pattern and the neighbor is used as the weight [47–49]. The most prevalent method to measure this distance is Euclidean. To measure the Euclidean distance between two vectors pi and pj, the equation mentioned in [50] will be used:(14)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
\usepackage{amssymb} 
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}\begin{equation*} D\left({p}_i,{p}_j\right)=\sqrt{\sum_{r=1}^n{\left({p}_{ir}-{p}_{jr}\right)}^2} \end{equation*}\end{document}

For the two-class (COVID-19/SARS-CoV and COVID-19/MERS-CoV) classifications, some effective evaluation parameters are calculated. They are accuracy (ACC), error rate, Matthews correlation coefficient (MCC) [53] and F1 score (the coordinated mean of precision and sensitivity) [54, 55] as follows:(15)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
\usepackage{amssymb} 
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}\begin{equation*} \mathrm{ACC}=\frac{\mathrm{Tp}+\mathrm{Tn}}{\mathrm{Tn}+\mathrm{Tn}+\mathrm{Fp}+\mathrm{Fn}}\times 100\% \end{equation*}\end{document}

(ACC: worst value = 0; best value = 100)(16)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
\usepackage{amssymb} 
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}\begin{equation*} \mathrm{Error}\ \mathrm{rate}=\frac{\mathrm{Fp}+\mathrm{Fn}}{\mathrm{Tn}+\mathrm{Tn}+\mathrm{Fp}+\mathrm{Fn}} \end{equation*}\end{document}

(Error rate: worst value = 1; best value = 0)(17)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
\usepackage{amssymb} 
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}\begin{equation*} \mathrm{MCC}=\frac{\left(\mathrm{Tp}\times \mathrm{Tn}\right)-\left(\mathrm{Fp}\times \mathrm{Fn}\right)}{\sqrt{\left(\mathrm{Tp}+\mathrm{Fp}\right)\left(\mathrm{Tp}+\mathrm{Fn}\right)\left(\mathrm{Tn}+\mathrm{Fp}\right)\left(\mathrm{Tn}+\mathrm{Fn}\right)}} \end{equation*}\end{document}

(MCC: worst value = −1; best value = +1)(18)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
